data.content:
**Yes, it works perfectly.** Both `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>` can be created via `stackalloc`:

```csharp
Span<nint>  s = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> u = stackalloc nuint[4];
```

Tested with .NET 10 — compiles and runs with no issues. On this 64-bit system, `nint.Size` is 8 bytes. Native-sized integers (`nint`/`nuint`) have been supported as first-class unmanaged types since C# 9 / .NET 5, which is what makes `stackalloc` with them valid.
